This collection contains the papers of David J. Toscano, a Democrat who served on the Charlottesville City Council from 1990-1998 and was the Mayor of Charlottesville from 1994-1996. During his tenure he
oversaw a multitude of issues including Charlottesville town reversion; 
the Meadow Creek Parkway; revitalization of West Main Street; 
cable television; fire and rescue services; the landfill and recycling; 
revenue sharing; transportation improvement; the attraction of "hi-tech" business; 
and a vision statement for Charlottesville 2025. Although he left City Council after two terms, Toscano remains active in Charlottesville politics.
